04/02/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Romanian Parliament opened its spring sessions Monday (3 February) and presented a set of law amendment priorities. 
According to the agenda of the next session, the parliament will discuss a bill for constitutional amendments in the statute and mandate of the presidency. 
Other legislative reforms include election laws, reforms related to the EU and NATO accession and energy supply regulations. 
Recent consultations among the parliamentary parties reached a general consensus for extending the mandate of the president from a four-year to five-year term and separation of the parliamentary and presidential elections. 
In the economic field, the parliament is expected to tackle tax and financial control legislation. 
(Rompres, Nine O'Clock - 04/02/03)
